  "technical_info": {
    "content": [
      "A TGA file consists of 2 main parts:\n\nHeaderColour Pixel information\n\nAll the values in a TGA file are in littl-endian as per the format specifications.",
      "The Targa format, which stands for Truevision Advanced Raster Graphics Adapter, was designed by Truevision (now Avid Technology) in 1984 for use with its first video software programs. The original format consisted of 2 areas:",
      "TGA File Header",
      "Image/Color Map Data",
      "While these two sections were included in the original 1984 specification of the Targa format, \"Developer Area,\" \"Extension Area,\" and \"TGA File Footer\" sections were added in 1989. This specification is known as the \"New TGA Format\" and consists of the following 5 areas:",
      "Image/ColorMap Data",
      "Developer Area",
      "Extension Area",
      "TGA File Footer",
      "Besides the three new sections of the image format, Truevision also introduced several new extensions to the Targa format in 1989 to meet the needs of graphics professionals. Examples of the extra extensions include:",
      "Date and time the file was created",
      "Author name and comments",
      "Alpha channel type",
      "Pixel aspect ratio",
      "Gamma value",
      "A scaled-down postage stamp copy of the image (a \"thumbnail\" image)"
    ]
  },
  "how_to_open": {
    "instructions": [
      "You can open TGA files with various image editors, such as Adobe Photoshop (multiplatform), ACD Systems Canvas (Windows), Corel Painter (multiplatform), and GIMP (multiplatform).",
      "If you are a Mac user, you can open TGA files with Apple Preview or Apple Photos, which come bundled with macOS. You can also convert TGA images to .JPEG, .PNG, .HEIC, .TIFF, and .PDF formats with Preview."
    ]
  },
  "how_to_convert": {
    "instructions": [
      "Many applications, including Adobe Photoshop, Corel PaintShop Pro, GIMP, and Apple Preview, can convert TGA files to other formats.",
      "For example, Adobe Photoshop can convert TGA files to many file types, including the following formats:",
      ".JPG - JPEG Image",
      ".PNG - Portable Network Graphic",
      ".TIF - Tagged Image File Format",
      ".GIF - Graphical Interchange Format",
      ".WEBP - WebP Image",
      ".BMP - Bitmap Image",
      ".DCM - DICOM Image",
      ".EPS - Encapsulated PostScript",
      ".PDF - Portable Document Format",
      ".PSD - Adobe Photoshop Document",
      ".AI - Adobe Illustrator Artwork"
    ]
  },
